divs: Sighting DetailsI was watching the news about 6:00pm when a strange light caut my attention thinking thats not a star its too light out. Is it a plane's head light,no its stayed in one spot.Went to get the camera and it was gone. Drove down to the lake where it was open sky and saw two strange lights one stationary one moving slowly I thought it was a plane's headlight but ruled it out as it moved right to left ever so slowly. There were alot of planes in the sky that night more than usual. I took some photos of the lights,planes,and stars and went home not thinking much about it until I looked at the photos the next day to compair. strange movement of light in still photo with a star in the shot not moving. STRANGE!!!! The light moving right to left also had strange movement.I know those planes saw this...
Summary: never seen that star befor, Its too light out to be a star, compared to star in photo, strange.
